reviewText: Eddie is a great talent but I thought this disc was a little disjointed for my taste. It's part concert,part documentary, part singing with others. It's also short at 60min. It was a very different crowd he was playing to than I expected to see. Certainly not a crowd you'd see at a Pearl Jam concert.When Eddy dished SUVs & Hummers the crowd went awfully quiet for a bit.Hmmm. I guess I feel the stuff he's done with Pearl Jam is really hard to follow, some of that stuff is amazing.
Title: Eddie Vedder: Water on the Road

reviewText: Great quality of sound and image, it captures the feeling, the energy in a EV solo concert. It feels realy intimate. Great way to celebreate 20 years as an artist
Title: Eddie Vedder: Water on the Road

reviewText: Can you name another iconic rock star who could pull off a performace like this one? I for one, think that Eddie Vedder's genuine personality and honest ability make him one of the very few who can. He comes out on the stage looking like the guy setting up to play on some street corner, but then he ends up touching and connecting to his audience in a profound way. Yeah, he's the guy from Pearl Jam, but on this stage he's even more of the real deal. Nothing comes across as flashy or pretentious. What he does is genuine and it's from the heart. And it is amazing.
summary: It Takes a Unique Character To Pull This Off, and Eddie Vedder Nails It!
Title: Eddie Vedder: Water on the Road

reviewText: Everyone has already done great reviews of this performance.  All I can say is it's one of the best intimate performances I've seen by any artist. Great set list, great choice of fellow artists, and the overall vibe is just fantastic. I've watched it multiple times already, and it just gets better each time.  The sound and video on the Blu-ray is just perfect, and it was filmed beautifully. The only thing I wish producers could do is get rid of the whooping sounds from the obligatory idiots in the audience, who always seem to be more focused on hearing themselves than expressing appreciation. I always imagine them playing it back for their friends as proof of their attendance:  "Hear that loud one?  That was ME, dude!" It always breaks the spell/kills the buzz at least temporarily.  Get a clue, guys.
Title: Eddie Vedder: Water on the Road

reviewText: I'm a huge fan of Pearl Jam's early CDs...hit and miss on the last 3-4 for me.  That said, Eddie Vedder is a very engaging, talented musician with a huge heart and a bigger conscious.  The editing/recording of this show was done very, very well.
summary: Excellent audio and video - Vedder a great talent
Title: Eddie Vedder: Water on the Road

reviewText: Really entertaining and fun. The picture quality and sound are good also. PJ and Eddie never put out a disappointing product. My only gripe is that their newer bootlegs are CD-R's which I find to be a waste of money. But, over all they put out quality products.

reviewText: Wow!  I just watched this entire DVD and I am blown away!  I probably have about 100 music DVD's but this one is very special.  The sound and picture are just excellent throughout and Eddie delivers a very intimate, great show.  I caught this tour in Albany, NY back in 2009 and enjoyed the show and hoped for a DVD and it's exceeded my expectations.  The DVD is probably more enjoyable than the show was as the concerts unfortunately drew in a ton of rowdy fans yelling through the whole show which admittedly sometimes is great fun, but these shows were for the most part acoustic and really deserved some quiet to hear the greatness.  The DVD takes care of this and you can really appreciate the great singing and playing Ed did for these shows.  The set list is great - "Into The Wild" is obviously featured heavily plus some great covers of Bob Dylan, The Beatles and Cat Stevens.  Pick this up immediately - you will not be disappointed.  It appears I'm the ninth reviewer, so far no one has put less than 5 stars on this - for good reason!
Title: Eddie Vedder: Water on the Road
